captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hi, guys.
It's Brooklyn and Bailey.

And today, we are
going to be showing

you guys some of
our favorite stuff
from the month of February.
-Mmhm.

-And it is snowing
down here in Texas,

so we have had two
days off of school.
Two days.
Hallelujah.
-It's been awesome.

-Also, don't forget,
guys, our meetup

is this Saturday, February
28, at PS from Aeropostale.

All the other information on it
will be in the description box
below.
So check that out.
And now, let's get started.

To start off, we're going to
show you our favorite pair
of shoes for this month.

We both picked a boot,
because it's kind of
been rainy and snowy down here.
So how about you start?
-OK.

These are some boots I actually
bought from my photo shoot,
our recent photo shoot in Utah.
And I absolutely love them.
They are so comfortable.
-She wears them every day.

-And they have a little heel,
because I'm super short.

So they help me look
a little bit taller.

And I got them from
Nordstrom Rack.

So if you guys want to go get
them, the link will be below.

-And then my boots
have a burned out toe.

They're kind of greyish, and
they've got a heel on them.

I love them because they
basically go with everything.

And I've literally worn
them with everything,
and it's not a joke.

And so I got these
from Nordstrom.

So these are adorbs,
and they're my favorite.

-Next up are our favorite
jackets from this month,

because as Bailey said, it's
been kind of cold and rainy.

And we haven't really needed
any use for jackets until now.
-Not really-- it's Texas.

-But recently we've
needed some jackets.
And so this is my favorite one.

I don't know if you can see all
the colors and designs on it.
It's actually really fun.

It's very bright and it goes
with just about anything

because there are so many colors
in here to match everything.
It's from Kingdom and State.

You guys can go buy it online,
or they have a store in Utah

if you guys want
to go there too.

-Yeah, all the links for
all the stuff in the video

will be in the
description box below.
-Yes.
-So you guys can look at that.

And so this is my
favorite jacket.

As you can see, it's
kind of a darkish green.

And then it's got black leather
on it-- black leather details.

And this one is
from H&M. I love it,

because first off, my
favorite color is green.

And then I just
like it because it

goes over everything
and it's leather
so it looks really nice.
And it's super cute.
-OK.

My favorite--
currently-- well, I just

barely figured out that
these even existed,
because they are so delicious.
No, I'm just kidding.

-I honestly-- I'm not
a huge fan of Ruffles.

But these are
actually really good.
-These are really good, yeah.

I figured these existed because
we were needing something
to eat while we were traveling.

So we went to a gas
station, and I found these,

and I was like
wait, I need those.

So ever since then I've
been kind of obsessed.
You can get these anywhere.

We got them from
Target, so yummy.

And then my next food item
is, for those of you--

I'm sure almost all of you
already know that I'm obsessed
with Reese's.

So my dad went to
the store-- Target--
and he found this for me.

And it's like a Reese's
version of Nutella.
BAILEY: Nutella.

And everybody
loves Nutella, so--

-Nobody scream, but
I don't like Nutella.

-Except for Brooklen--
who doesn't like Nutella.
-So I found this.

My dad found this
for me so I can
use this in place of Nutella.
And I'm super excited.

It's just like the
Reese's spread,
so you can put it on whatever.

-And then I really love
like fruity candies,
like Starburst and Skittles.

So I found these
Orchard Skilttles.

And they're basically
like the flavors of things
you would find in an orchard.
-Red apple.
-Like lime, cherry.
-Orange.
-Red apple.
-Peach.
-Peach!
That's her favorite.
-Which is my favorite.
I love peach.

So these are just like
some fun little snacks.
And yeah.

-As you can see,
this bottle is empty

because I used it
all this month.

But this is my new
favorite conditioner,

because my hair is super
long and super thick

and it's really hard to
take care of and whatever.

But I found this conditioner
that works really well.
And it's Suave's.
And-- let's see.
What is it called?

Almond Plus Shea
Butter Conditioner.
Yeah, 100% natural.
-It smells so-- it's so good.
-It smells so good.

-Even if you blow dry your
hair after your shower,
you can still smell it.
It's so good.
-Yeah.

I'll take my hair
out of a ponytail,
and I'm like-- that smells good.
-It's so good.

-You just get a whiff
of deliciousness.

But I don't know if you'd
want to eat conditioner.

-I don't think you want
to eat conditioner.

-But I absolutely
love this conditioner.

-And then for my hair
product, I have the Big
and Sexy Hair Powder Play.

And I like this, because you
know sometimes you just need
that volume in your hair?

You just need it there
and it's not coming?

Then you can just put a
little bit of this in there
and it will work perfectly.

And so I've been loving this,
because volume, it never hurts.
So I use this all the time.

-This is my new favorite
book of February.

I read it because we were
flying to and from California
and Utah.

So I had a bunch of time, so
I was able to read this book.
And I know it's kind of old.
I don't know.
But I thought it was super good.
I'd never read it before.
-I've actually not read it yet.
-It's really kid friendly.

There's lots of just--
it's just intriguing.

And it's really
good for any ages,
because there is nothing bad.
-It is adventure?
What is it?

-It's about Michael
Vey, and he's

got these powers, these
electrical powers.

And he has to search-- these
bad people are coming after him

because he has powers and he
has to go search for his mom

because they kidnapped
her and all this stuff.
-Oh.
-So it's really good.
I really liked it.

I'm currently reading
the second one.

So if you guys want a good
book, this is a good one.
-I might read it.

So you all know I'm
obsessed with Disney.
It's almost bad.

So Brooklyn got me this
phone case for Christmas.

Well, actually, it
didn't come for a while.

So that's why it's my
favorite for this month,

because it didn't
come for Christmas.

But it's basically got all
these Disney characters on it--

the princesses, Tinker Bell,
Hakuna Matata, Lilo and Stitch.
-Belle.
-The Jungle Book.
101 Dalmatians.
-Pinocchio.

-All of these different
characters-- and so the link

for this will be in
the description box
just like everything else.
But I love this phone case.

So it's definitely
one of my favorites.
-You're welcome.
All right.

Next up, recently
because it's been so cold

everywhere I've been traveling,
I've needed a lot of chapstick,

because my lips get so dry
and I'm just sick of it.

And my friend, she
knows that I was sick,

and she gave me some
of this chapstick.

And ever since, I've been using
it, and I absolutely love it.

And it's called Burt's--
is it Burt's Bees?
I almost said birthday bees.
It's Burt's Bees chapstick.
And it smells like--

-Well, there's
different flavors?
-Is it?
-So it smells different.
But this one's peppermint.

-Oh, this one is--
oh, I didn't even

know there were
different flavors.
-There are different flavors.
-Weird.

OK, so apparently, there
are different flavors.
I didn't know that.
This one's peppermint.

The one I have currently smells
like pineapple or something,
something fruity.
-Oh.
-It smells good.
Go figure.
-I might have to steal that.

-So if you guys need good
chapstick, this is a good one.
-OK.

So my next item
is a make up bag.
And we found this at Forever 21.

I was shopping around with
my mom and my Aunt Jenny.
And so they found this.

And at first, my mom
was like, no, no, no.
It's mine.
-That's mine.

-And then she's like,
well, it doesn't really
fit my personality.
So then she gave it to me.

And I think it fits
my personality.
-Pretty well.
-And it's super cute.
It's super cute.
So this is my new make up bag.
This-- I love it so much.
-Yeah, it's cute.

Now, I have two bags
from Tar-zhay-- Target.
-Tar-zhay.

-And the first one is
this little brown one.
Can you see it?

It's got this cute
little clasp thing.

You push up, and then
you can pull it open.

-It almost reminds me of
a lock for some reason.
-It reminds me of a saddle bag.
-Oh, yeah.
-I don't know.
It's cute.

I thought it was cute,
because it's little

and you can just
carry it around.
And it's across the body.

So it's just like hanging
at your hip all the time.

And brown goes with almost
basically everything.
Everything.

-So you could just match it
with whatever and it's cute.

You can get it from
Target if you want it.
It's adorable.

And then my next bag
is this black one.
And it's like a mini backpack.
BAILEY: I love that bag.

-And I think someone we
saw the other had this on.

And so we were like, oh, my
gosh, where'd you get that?
I want it.
So we went to Target-- again.
And we bought this.
And it was super adorable.

And I think I'm just
gonna use it for traveling
and stuff, because it's just--

-It's a little too
small for school stuff.

-It's too small for school,
but it's got lots of room
for all my traveling gear.
And it's cute.

So I can just carry this
around an airport, whatevs.

And so I'm super
excited to use it.

-So my next thing is something
that I put in my room.
And it's from my best friend.

She gave it to me, and
it's from Altered State.

And it says, "Friends will
help you up when you fall,

but best friends will push
you back down and laugh."

And I thought that was
hysterical, because honestly--
-It's absolutely true.

-That's absolutely 100
bazillion percent true.

It's like best friends,
they're like-- psh.

-No, best friends would
be the ones who fall.

And then when you try to help
them up, they pull you down.
-That's exactly.

So this is adorable and I
love it, having it in my room.
OK.

This necklace is
from Forever 21.

And it's like a
two-piece necklace.
It kind of goes like that.

And I have been loving it,
because the colors are really
fun.
It's like blue and gray and tan.
And it matches the season.

-Well, and it's
cool, because you

can wear one half of
it or the other half.
-Or the other half of it.
-Or both of them together.
-Or together.

And so this is just
a really fun necklace
that I found at Forever 21.
So there's that.

And then last, but not least,
we've got our nail polishes.
-Tah-dah.

BAILEY: And of course,
we picked Essie,
because Essie is the best.
BROOKLYN: Essie is the bomb.

-So I picked a light pink,
and it's called Mademoiselle.

And I love this
one, just because it
matches my personality.
I'm totally a pinkie person.
-It's true.

So basically, all the
pinks appeal to me,

so this one was obviously
one of my first picks.
-And I am a completely blue fan.

So of course, this
one appealed to me.

And this is called
Butler, Please.
-They go together.
Mademoiselle.
-And Butler, Please.
-Except for I'm the butler.
Whatever.

That's OK with me,
I like the color.
But it's super adorable.

And it's just a really
pretty indigo color.
And I absolutely love it.
And I'm just so excited.

-Thank you guys so much for
watching our February Favorites
video.

If you want to see
more videos like this,
don't forget to subscribe.

Also, give this
video a thumbs up.

-Be sure to leave a comment
below on one of your February

favorites so we can try
out some of your stuff.
-Yes.

-And we'll see you
guys next week.
Bye.
-Bye.
